line_1: Nor fisks the Tail, or fawns at gentle Stroaks.
line_2: Nor licks the bounteous Hand, (ev'n Love provokes)

line_1: Tho' swift their Pace, tho' Fate attends their Strokes,
line_2: A worthless Fly the mighty Fish provokes.

line_1: See, how's she spent, and sinks beneath their strokes
line_2: The Miller, whom this most of all provokes,

line_1: Straight the small Ministers fetch nimble Strokes,
line_2: And fresh Vermillion dy'd his Languid Looks;
